sentence: Home Depot ( HD ) is attracting the attention of option bulls Monday.
So far, 1,929 contracts of the Dec. 14-expiring 177.50 call have change hands against open interest of 556 contracts.
Pricing on today's trades indicates that these new contracts were initiated from the buy side.
IK-> The technicals for HD ($168.76 down $4.11) are bearish with a downward trend.
Look at the Jan. 140/145 bull-put spread for a 25-cent credit.
That's a 5.3% return and the stock has to fall by 14.1% to cause a problem.
